Manchester United  beat Chelsea 2-1
to move into the semifinals of soccerâ€™s Champions League, while
Barcelona advanced with a 1-0 win over Shakhtar Donetsk.  Javier Hernandez and Park Ji-Sung scored to give United a
3-1 win over the two-game quarterfinal. Didier Drogba scored for
Chelsea, which had Ramires sent off in the 70th minute.
Manchester United will face Schalke or defending champion Inter
Milan in the semifinals.  Lionel Messi  scored as Barcelona completed a 6-1 series win
over Shakhtar Donetsk. Barcelona will play rival Real Madrid or
Tottenham in the final four.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
